laboratory_examinations.findings: This culture contains mixed bacterial types (>=3) so an abbreviated workup is performed. Any growth of P.aeruginosa, S.aureus and beta hemolytic streptococci will be reported. If these bacteria are not reported, they are not present in this culture.

The cerebral sulci, ventricles, and extra-axial CSF-containing spaces are mildly enlarged, in keeping with age-related volume loss. The gray-white matter differentiation is well preserved. There is no CT evidence of acute ischemic infarct, intracranial hemorrhage or space-occupying lesion. Periventricular confluent low attenuation is consistent with sequela of small vessel ischemic disease. The cystic lesion involving the pineal gland with peripheral calcification is unchanged since ___ and likely represents a simple cyst.
